Getting #avobowl game ready 🏈 @metemgee Jerk Shrimp Salad featuring DESBRY tropical avocados 
⁣
INGREDIENTS :⁣
1 tropical DESBRY avocado, diced⁣
1 yellow mango, diced ⁣
1/2 small red onion sliced⁣
1/4 cup of cilantro leaves⁣
1 English cucumber, diced ⁣
2 cups of mixed greens⁣
FOR THE JERK SHRIMP:⁣
1 lb of medium sized shrimp⁣
2 tablespoons of Jerk Seasoning (I used my homemade @whole30 compatible jerk seasoning that you can find at Metemgee.com)⁣
Salt to taste⁣
Cooking spray ⁣
Salad dressing of your choice. I used @tessemaes Italian dressing. ⁣
⁣
INSTRUCTIONS:⁣
COMBINE the shrimp with the jerk seasoning and a pinch of salt in a bowl and let marinate for 15 minutes ⁣
SPRAY air fryer basket or tray with cooking spray then add the shrimp and air fry for 5 minutes at 450 °F ⁣
COMBINE all of the salad ingredients into a large salad and toss together, then top with the jerk shrimp and serve. ⁣

🌮 It’s TACO TUESDAY! Try these delicious baked vegab avocado tacos! You’re going to LOVE the super flavorful and SPICY cauliflower with an Indian flair all smothered in cheese and creamy avocadoooo goodness 🥑🌮✨🤷🏻‍♀️

Here’s what you’ll need: 
Stack of corn tortillas
Spiced Roasted Cauliflower
Mexican shredded cheese
Avocado crema 
Scallions // cilantro
Pickled red onions

✨Spiced Roasted Cauliflower✨
1 head yellow/orangey cauliflower 
2 Tbsp curry powder 
1 Tbsp cumin 
2 Tsp garlic powder 
2 Tsp onion powder
Salt 
Pepper 
Olive oil 

✨Avocado Crema✨
1 large DESBRY avocado 
2 Tbsp Mayo
1 clove garlic 
1 Tbsp juice from jar of pickled red onions
Salt
Pepper

- METHOD -
1. Prep the cauliflower and get it in the oven 
2. Make the avocado crema in the food processor
3. Hit the tortillas with a little 🔥 so they are pliable for filling 
4. Line a baking sheet with foil or parchment 
5. Prepare the tacos by layering each tortilla with crema, cauli, more crema, then cheese and scallions and pickled red onions. Stack them on the baking sheet. 
6. Drizzle the tortillas lightly with olive oil to and bake in the oven at 425 for about 7 minutes on each side 
7. Serve right off the sheet pan for a super easy weeknight meal for the family! 

🌮🥑✨🫶🌮🥑✨

.
.

Whipping up some #gameday #avobowl brunch ideas with @chef_timineri. 🥑 

INGREDIENTS

2 Desbry avocados
4 eggs
½ cup grated cheese (your favorite)
Sea salt and fresh ground pepper, to taste

DIRECTIONS:

1.Cut each avocado in half and remove the seed. Preheat oven to 400 degrees. 
2. Cut a small slice on the bottom of each avocado half to create a flat surface so they won’t roll. 
3.Crack an egg into each avocado half where the seed was. 
4.Season the top of the avocado and egg with salt and pepper to taste. Evenly add the shredded cheese to the top of each avocado. 
5.Bake stuffed avocados for 10 to 15 minutes or until the egg reaches the desired doneness. 
6.Remove avocados from oven and serve with toast.

Our favorite go to #gameday guacamole. Check out our recipe below.

Ingredients
2 DESBRY avocados, (pit and skin removed) diced small 
2 tomatoes, diced small 
2 Key limes, juiced 
1 bell pepper, (seeds removed) diced small 
1/2 red onion, diced small 
1/3 cup fresh cilantro, roughly chopped 
1 tablespoon taco seasoning 
1 tablespoon olive oil 
Several dashes Florida hot sauce, to taste 
Sea salt and fresh ground pepper, to taste 

Directions:
1.Mix all the ingredients together in a large bowl and stir to combine. 
2.Taste and adjust seasoning as needed. 
3.Store in an air-tight container in the refrigerator until ready to use. 
4. Serve cold with sliced Florida vegetables and tortilla chips.

THE #tropicalsalad 🤩 @theproducemoms 
Your family will love the flavors of this Tropical Fruit Salad! Packed with tropical fruit flavors & a simple honey dressing it’s simply delicious! Plus, it is served in a Tropical Avocado for an extra special touch! We call it an Avo-Bowl!

Whether you are looking to try a new fruit salad or simply want to impress your guests, this tropical fruit salad packs a punch that is full of flavor. The sweetness of the PinkGlow® Pineapple, mango and dragon fruit mixed with the creaminess of the Desbry® Tropical Avocado and the zest of the lime juice will have people asking for this recipe over and over again.

To present your tropical fruit salad, keep the skins from the Desbry® Tropical Avocado to serve it in! Why dirty bowls if we don’t have to! Plus, who doesn’t love a good Avo-Bowl recipe? 

Ingredients 
2 Desbry® Tropical Avocados, cubed – keep skins to serve salad
1 Dragon Fruit, cubed
1 Mango, peeled & diced
1 PinkGlow® Pineapple, diced
4-6 kumquats, thinly sliced
1 Starfruit
⅓ cup shredded coconut

Dressing

¼ cup honey
1 ½ Tablespoon fresh lime juice
1 tablespoon lime zest

Directions: 
In a large bowl, combine all the fruit.
In a small bowl, whisk honey, lime juice and zest together. Drizzle dressing over the top of the fresh fruit.
Gently toss to combine. Let it sit for 20 minutes before serving.
Scoop tropical fruit salad into Desbry® Tropical Avocado skins. Finally, cover with shredded coconut and serve.

Healthy tacos are on the menu: Taco Stuffed Florida Avocado @freshfromflorida 

INGREDIENTS
4 ripe Florida DESBRY avocados 

1 pound Florida ground beef 

1 large Florida tomato, diced (about 1 cup) 

1 teaspoon cooking oil 

2 tablespoons fresh cilantro, chopped 

2 tablespoon taco seasoning, plus more to taste 

1 cup salsa 

2 limes, quartered 

1/2 medium onion, diced small (about 1 cup) 

1 cup sour cream 

1 cup Jack cheese, shredded 

PREPARATION
Preheat a medium skillet over medium–high heat. Add the cooking oil to the preheated pan, then add onions and cook for 3 to 5 minutes or until caramelized. Carefully add the ground beef and continue to cook, using a spatula or wooden spoon to break up the ground beef as it cooks completely. Add the taco seasoning and diced tomato, stir and carefully drain any excess fat. Taste and adjust seasoning as needed. Remove the taco meat from the heat to cool slightly. Use a kitchen knife to carefully cut each avocado in half, removing the large seed in the middle and continue this process for all 4 avocados. Use half of a lime to squeeze juice over each of the cut avocados. Lightly season each cut avocado with more taco seasoning. Evenly add the same amount of taco meat to each avocado half. Garnish each stuffed avocado with shredded cheese, salsa, fresh cilantro, lime quarters and sour cream.
.

The dreamiest Mango and Passionfruit cheesecake we’ve EVER seen! @cherylshealthylife 

Recipe 👇🏻

One bite will send you right to the tropics 🏝️ There are 3 layers here but so easy & everything goes right into your blender. The crust is very forgiving too as you can use your favorite graham cracker crust instead. 
IB: @rainbownourishments 

CRUST:
5 dates soaked for 10 min in hot water 
1/2 cup raw almonds 
1/2 cup raw pecans 
1/2 cup coconut flakes 
pinch of salt & cinnamon 

FILLING:
2 cups of cashews soaked in hot water for 10 min 
2 honey mangoes or 1 large ripe mango 
1 cup thick coconut yogurt 
1/3 cup maple syrup 
1/3 cup cacao butter or coconut oil melted (coconut oil will make it softer) 
1/4 cup lemon juice or the pulp of 2 passionfruits 
1 tsp vanilla 
pinch of salt 

TOP LAYER:
3 honey mangoes or 2 large mangoes 
pulp of 2 passionfruits or 1 lemon juiced 
2 tbsp arrowroot powder 

Line an 8x8 baking dish with parchment & set aside. Add the nuts to a food processor & pulse into very fine pieces. Add the soaked dates discarding the liquid & coconut flakes. Blend until the mixture becomes sticky then transfer to the baking dish. Using damp hands press down until it’s even & smooth-place in the fridge while you make the filling. For the filling scoop out all of the mango flesh & add all of the ingredients into a high-powered blender & blend until smooth. Pour on top of the crust & smooth out with a spatula. Place in the fridge for a minimum of 4hrs or overnight. The top layer you will blend the mango flesh in the same blender until smooth & add to a small sauce-pot along with the passionfruit flesh or lemon with 2 tbsp arrowroot. Place on medium heat & whisk until smooth, once it starts to boil keep mixing until it thickens about 5 min. Take off heat & let cool completely before you pour this over the filling. Once you poured it over the filling let it chill in the fridge for another 30 min. Cut into 12 pieces using a wet knife. Leftovers keep well in the fridge or freezer.
Enjoy! 
.
.

These Drizzled Manzanos are all our summer dreams come true. Four decadent drizzles (coconut cream, peanut butter, red dragon smoothie and dark chocolate) give a whole new meaning to frozen treats. The secret? Freeze the bananas first so that the drizzles harden immediately and keep their shape.

You can make these Drizzled Manzanos as indulgent or as nourishing as you like. My version is vegan, whole food, and low in sugar thanks to unsweetened natural PB and dark chocolate.

My top tips for making these Drizzled Bananas:
🌈 Freeze the bananas overnight so they’re fully frozen
🌈 Leave them in the freezer until the last possible minute; the colder the banana, the faster the drizzle will harden (= neater drizzles)
🌈 Make sure the drizzles are just barely warm; you want them to have a nice, thin, drippy texture but to harden as quickly as possible
🌈 Let each drizzle harden for about 30 seconds before adding the next one so they don’t mix

BAKED YUCA FRIES• @seecandycook 

These oven fries are so crispy & flavorful and the yuca adds such a delicious depth of flavor.  If you’re looking for something new to add into your side dish rotation, these are it! 

INGREDIENTS:
2 large DESBRY yuca roots 
olive oil
fresh thyme
salt/pepper (including flaky sea salt)
Tony Chacheres original seasoning

HOW TO:
1. Preheat oven to 400°
2. Peel your yuca and make sure no skin remains. 
3. Cut into strips for fries.  Then boil for 8 min.  You want them slightly tender.
4. Remove from water and air dry for 5-10 minutes. 
5. Toss with olive oil and seasonings to coat.
6. Place spread out on baking sheet and bake for 30 min. 
7. Remove from oven and top with fresh thyme and flaky sea salt.
8. Serve with your favorite dipping sauce! I used my Canes copycat sauce! Enjoy! 

✨the best fall roots selection from @tropicalfruitboxusa !✨

INGREDIENTS:
2 large DESBRY yuca roots 
olive oil
fresh thyme
salt/pepper (including flaky sea salt)
Tony Chacheres original seasoning

HOW TO:
1. Preheat oven to 400°
2. Peel your yuca and make sure no skin remains. 
3. Cut into strips for fries.  Then boil for 8 min.  You want them slightly tender.
4. Remove from water and air dry for 5-10 minutes. 
5. Toss with olive oil and seasonings to coat.
6. Place spread out on baking sheet and bake for 30 min. 
7. Remove from oven and top with fresh thyme and flaky sea salt.
8. Serve with your favorite dipping sauce! I used my Canes copycat sauce! Enjoy!
